            <thetext>Add a generator command line option to pass in global &#39;let&#39; macros and their 
values when invoking the generator. 

This is beneficial to override existing values, or add new values on the fly. 
As these macros are available early in the generator (before any job is being 
constructed), they can be used in top-level &quot;include&quot; keys (that&#39;s the current 
use case).

Mind that this only affects the global &#39;let&#39; section of the main configuration 
file (&#39;config.json&#39; or what you pass with the &#39;-c&#39; option).</thetext>
